# EmpathAI – Spring Boot REST API Backend Plan

## Overview
This document maps the **existing React frontend** to a **Java Spring Boot backend** covering three admin modules:
1. **User Management** (Admin Panel)
2. **Feelings Explorer** (Questionnaire / Assessments)
3. **Curriculum Management**

---

## 1. Tech Stack & Project Setup

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| Framework | Spring Boot 3.x |
| Language | Java 17+ |
| Build Tool | Maven or Gradle |
| Database | PostgreSQL (recommended) or MySQL |
| ORM | Spring Data JPA + Hibernate |
| Security | Spring Security + JWT |
| API Docs | SpringDoc OpenAPI (Swagger UI) |
| Validation | Jakarta Validation (`@Valid`) |
| Password | BCryptPasswordEncoder |

### Spring Initializr Dependencies
```
- Spring Web
- Spring Data JPA
- Spring Security
- PostgreSQL Driver
- Spring Boot DevTools
- Validation
- Lombok
- SpringDoc OpenAPI (manual add)
```

---

## 2. Domain / Entity Models

### 2.1 User (Polymorphic – Single Table Inheritance)
```
User (base)
├── id (Long)
├── name (String)
├── email (String, unique)
├── passwordHash (String)
├── role (Enum: STUDENT, SCHOOL_ADMIN, PSYCHOLOGIST, CONTENT_ADMIN, SUPER_ADMIN)
├── phoneNumber (String)
├── createdAt (LocalDateTime)
└── updatedAt (LocalDateTime)

Student extends User
├── className (String)  // "4th Standard"
├── school (String)
├── parentName (String)
├── dateOfBirth (LocalDate)
├── address (String)
├── bloodGroup (String)
└── emergencyContact (String)

SchoolAdmin extends User
└── school (String)

Psychologist extends User
└── licenseId (String)

ContentAdmin extends User
└── department (Enum: CURRICULUM, ASSESSMENT, TECHNICAL)
```

### 2.2 Curriculum / Syllabus
```
Syllabus
├── id (Long)
├── subject (String)
├── classLevel (String)  // "10th Standard"
├── createdAt / updatedAt
└── modules (List<LearningModule>)

LearningModule
├── id (Long)
├── syllabus (ManyToOne → Syllabus)
├── title (String)
├── videoUrl (String)
├── summary (String)
├── summaryImageUrl (String)
├── orderIndex (Integer)
├── learningObjectives (List<String> → @ElementCollection)
└── quizQuestions (List<QuizQuestion>)

QuizQuestion
├── id (Long)
├── module (ManyToOne → LearningModule)
├── questionText (String)
├── imageUrl (String, nullable)
├── options (List<String> → @ElementCollection)
├── correctAnswerIndex (Integer)
└── explanation (String)
```

### 2.3 Feelings Explorer (Assessment / Questionnaire)
```
AssessmentQuestion
├── id (Long)
├── questionText (String)
├── questionType (Enum: SCALE, MEMORY, TEXT)
├── options (List<AssessmentOption>)
└── orderIndex (Integer)

AssessmentOption
├── id (Long)
├── question (ManyToOne → AssessmentQuestion)
├── label (String)
├── value (Integer)
└── emotionType (Enum: HAPPY, NEUTRAL, CONCERN, SAD)

AssessmentResponse (stores a student's completed assessment)
├── id (Long)
├── student (ManyToOne → Student)
├── submittedAt (LocalDateTime)
└── answers (List<AnswerRecord>)

AnswerRecord
├── id (Long)
├── response (ManyToOne → AssessmentResponse)
├── question (ManyToOne → AssessmentQuestion)
└── answerValue (String)  // numeric or JSON array for memory
```

---

## 3. REST API Endpoints

### 3.1 Authentication
```
POST   /api/auth/login           → { email, password } → { token, user }
POST   /api/auth/refresh          → { refreshToken } → { token }
POST   /api/auth/logout
POST   /api/auth/reset-password   → { userId, newPassword }
```

### 3.2 User Management (Admin only)
```
GET    /api/users                → List all users (filter by ?role=student&school=X)
POST   /api/users                → Create user (role-specific body)
GET    /api/users/{id}           → Get user by ID (with extended profile)
PUT    /api/users/{id}           → Update user
DELETE /api/users/{id}           → Soft-delete user
POST   /api/users/{id}/reset-password → Admin resets a user's password

# School grouping (for student tab)
GET    /api/users/schools         → [{ schoolName, studentCount }]
GET    /api/users/by-school/{school} → All students in a school
```

### 3.3 Curriculum Management
```
GET    /api/syllabi               → List all syllabi (filter ?classLevel=10th Standard)
POST   /api/syllabi               → Create syllabus
GET    /api/syllabi/{id}          → Get syllabus with modules
PUT    /api/syllabi/{id}          → Update syllabus
DELETE /api/syllabi/{id}          → Delete syllabus

GET    /api/syllabi/{id}/modules         → List modules for a syllabus
POST   /api/syllabi/{id}/modules         → Add module
GET    /api/syllabi/{id}/modules/{modId} → Get module detail (with quiz)
PUT    /api/syllabi/{id}/modules/{modId} → Update module
DELETE /api/syllabi/{id}/modules/{modId} → Delete module

# Quiz
GET    /api/modules/{modId}/quiz         → Get quiz questions
PUT    /api/modules/{modId}/quiz         → Replace all quiz questions
```

### 3.4 Feelings Explorer (Questionnaire)
```
GET    /api/questionnaire/questions      → Get all questions (ordered)
POST   /api/questionnaire/submit         → Submit completed assessment
GET    /api/questionnaire/responses      → Admin: list all responses
GET    /api/questionnaire/responses/{studentId} → Student's history
GET    /api/questionnaire/responses/{id}/report → Report for one session
```

